h3. Issue Summary

When doing the following steps in a custom editor (add {{editor}} attribute in your {{dynamicMacro}} module):

# Use confluence.saveMacro to save plain-text macro params and body: 
{code}
AP.confluence.saveMacro({foo : 'bar'}, "foo: bar saved!");
{code}
# Call getMacroData and getMacroBody.
# Notice that getMacroData and getMacroBody does not return anything upon saving the macro.
# Only when you refresh will you get the updated one. See video:
 [^ReplicationVideo-480.mov] 

h3. Expected Results
getMacroData and getMacroBody should return saved changes upon confluence.saveMacro

h3. Actual Results
getMacroData and getMacroBody does not return anything upon saving the macro.

h3. Notes
* Sample snippets from app developer:

{code}
export const Editor = () => {  
const [version] = useState(0);  
const [tabs] = useState([]);  
const onSubmit = useCallback(() => {    
    if (event.button.name !== 'submit') {      return;    }    
    AP.confluence.saveMacro({version: version + 1}, JSON.stringify(tabs));    
    AP.confluence.closeMacroEditor();  
    }, [tabs, version]);  

    useEffect(() => {    
        AP.events.on('dialog.button.click', onSubmit);    
        return () => {      
            AP.events.offAll('dialog.button.click');    
        };  
    }, [onSubmit]);  
    return <Tabs tabs={tabs} />;
};
{code}

{code}
export const View = () => {  
    const [tabs, setTabs] = useState([]);  
    useEffect(() => {    
        AP.confluence.getMacroBody(body => setTabs(JSON.parse(body)));  
    }, 
    []);  
    return <Tabs tabs={tabs} />;
};
{code}

h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h2. Issue Summary:

A bug was reported and fixed in CONFCLOUD-65548 that was reproduced as follows:

Run the following javascript (from browser console) inside the context of a connect confluence macro editor:
{code:java}
var opts = {
  "title": "Title",
  "body": "Some body",
  "type": "warning"
};
AP.flag.create(opts);{code}
*Expected Results:*  A flag is displayed with the correct title and body
h2. Request:  

Create an integration test to verify that Flag requests coming in from Connect Macros result in a Confluence flag being shown.
